    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-11-28T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-11-28T14:00:00-05:00" n="451"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d451">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">460.509/11–2851: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bonsal</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-11-28T20:00:00+01:00"
                            >November 28, 1951—8 p. m</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3189. No distribution outside Dept. For Camp and Vernon. <gloss
                        target="#t_Excon1">Excon</gloss>. <gloss target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss>
                    informed today that Harriman has (1) agreed make primary lists available all
                    countries, in view Dept concurrence; (2) agreed leave question of classification
                    open until he returns in second week Dec; and (3) signed title II “short list”
                    as originally prepared, with addition item 2073, owing to strong views expressed
                    by other agencies and Cong Battle. <gloss target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss>
                    understands Harriman not convinced on merits “short list” as against long and
                    desires discuss matter further when returns.</p>
                <p>Longer list II which <gloss target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss> was asked prepare
                    has been given Tannenwald, who is leaving tomorrow.</p>
                <p>Sent Dept 3189, rptd info Rome 257 for Linder.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bonsal</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
